This repository contains automated tests for user registration, authorization, and issue creation on a website using the Playwright testing library.

Installation:
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/petrenko-do/playwright_redmine_testing

Running Tests:
To run the tests, use the following command:
npx playwright test

Test Descriptions:
User Registration Test: Validates the registration process with valid user data.
User Authorization Test: Checks the authorization process with valid credentials.
Invalid Authorization Test: Validates the error message when invalid credentials are provided.
Search Test: Tests the search functionality with specific keywords and filters.
Create Question Test: Tests the issue creation process in Redmine.

Data Files:
userData.json: Contains valid user registration data.
invalidUserData.json: Contains invalid user credentials for testing authorization failures.
searchData.json: Contains search keywords used in the search test.
createQuestionData.json: Contains data related to issue types, statuses, categories, and versions.

Classes:
SignUpPage: Handles interactions with the user registration page.
AuthPage: Manages elements on the user login page.
InvalidAuthPage: Manages elements on the invalid login page.
SearchPage: Handles the search functionality on the page.
CreateQuestion: Manages the creation of new questions in Redmine.